content.body:
### Shop 235/85R16 Tire Size
The 235/85R16 tire size was pretty prevalent on light trucks in the 80s and 90s, and could be found on vehicles like the Chevrolet R2500 Suburban, Dodge Ram 3500, Ford F-250 Super Duty, and GMC R3500.

Popular vehicles:
1989-1991 Chevrolet R2500 Suburban
2000-2002 Dodge Ram 3500
1999-2004 Ford F-250 Super Duty
1987-1991 GMC R3500

All-season tires are designed to give drivers consistent performance in dry, wet, and light winter weather conditions, which makes them a popular choice for drivers. Take a look at the Bridgestone Dueler H/T 685, General Grabber HTS60, and [GT Radial Savero HT2](https://simpletire.com/brands/gt-radial-tires/savero-ht2) if you’re looking for a set of 235/85R16 tires that are built to perform year-round.

Drivers of larger trucks sometimes take their ride off-road so they need a set of tires that can handle any terrain. All-terrain tires are built to perform on- and off-road, so consider the [Yokohama Geolandar AT G015](https://simpletire.com/brands/yokohama-tires/geolandar-at-g015), Falken Wildpeak A/T3W, or Nokian Outpost AT if you want a set of 235/85R16 tires that performs on any terrain.

While all-terrain tires are built to perform on- and off-road, they might struggle in deep mud or tough rocks. Fortunately, mud terrain tires are designed to perform in tough off-road conditions and tires like the BFGoodrich Mud-Terrain T/A KM3, [Kumho Road Venture MT71](https://simpletire.com/brands/kumho-tires/road-venture-mt71), and Toyo Open Country M/T are a great choice for light trucks that do a lot of off-road driving.

235/85R16 could also be a trailer tire size. Consider the Prometer ST Radial, [LingLong F835 (All Steel)](https://simpletire.com/brands/linglong-tires/f835-all-steel), and Hi Run JK42 Trailer is you need a new set of 235/85R16 trailer tires.

Whether you drive a Chevrolet R2500 Suburban, Dodge Ram 3500, Ford F-250 Super Duty, GMC R3500, or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 235/85R16 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
